    • Constructor Detail

      • DataCollectionRealTimeSnapshotSequence

        public DataCollectionRealTimeSnapshotSequence(DataCollectionSequence sequence,
                                      int minutesBack,
                                      boolean includeErrorEventItems,
                                      boolean getErrorEventItemsOnly)
        Create a new initialized instance. This constructor is called by the load test program only.
        Parameters:
        sequence - the data collection sequence
        minutesBack - relative point of time in the past (in minutes) from which collecting of the measured items starts, or -1 = from the beginning of the load test execution
        includeErrorEventItems - if false then don't include error event items
        getErrorEventItemsOnly - if true then get only error event items
        See Also:
        DataCollectionAbstractItem.ITEM_TYPE_ERROR_EVENT

      • DataCollectionRealTimeSnapshotSequence

        public DataCollectionRealTimeSnapshotSequence()
        Create an empty instance - used for object transfer.

    • Method Detail

      • getClusterOptions

        public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.String> getClusterOptions()
        Get a hash map about all configured cluster options.
        The <Integer> keys of the hash map contain the options.
        The <String> values of the hash map contain the new diagram sub title for the merged data, or null if no new diagram sub title is required.
        See Also:
        DataCollectionSequence.CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_SUM, DataCollectionSequence.CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_SUM_LASTVALID, DataCollectionSequence.CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_AVERAGE, DataCollectionSequence.CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_AVERAGE_LASTVALID

      • getItemType

        public int getItemType()
        Return the data item type of the sequence. Note that ITEM_TYPE_ERROR_EVENT can be mixed into the same sequence with any other data item type. Therefore this method never return as result ITEM_TYPE_ERROR_EVENT.
        Returns:
        the data item type of the sequence, or the default value = ITEM_TYPE_NOTYPE if no item type was set AND/OR no measurement items have added to the sequence.
        See Also:
        DataCollectionAbstractItem.ITEM_TYPE_NOTYPE, DataCollectionAbstractItem.ITEM_TYPE_FLOAT_VALUE, DataCollectionAbstractItem.ITEM_TYPE_YZ_FLOAT_VALUE, DataCollectionAbstractItem.ITEM_TYPE_TEXT_FRAGMENT, getFloatItems(), getYZFloatItems(), getTextItems()
